<br>
Is your swimming maxed (asking that for curiosity only)? I've noticed that for some stupid reason I can outswim water based creatures (like sharks) but not land based creatures that happen to be in water. I think to make creatures that can work in both water and land, they have to make the land based and just have them ignore the water all together, hence they are swimming (running actualy) at a dry land running pace. It's pretty dumb to have orcs and goblins of a much lower level than me (green and blue cons) out swiming me when my swimming is maxed for my level.<br>
<br>
I have to give a big <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /rude</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to Verant on this one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ...and fighting underwater is a pain since when at 0 stamina, medding is impossible.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Really? Did not know that. I could have sworn I have meditated under water before. Hmmm...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Swim out to the coloums then swim down and cast an earth pet...</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
You can coax your pet into the water. I've done this when leveling up to 28/29. I would swim out and med by the columns (you can sit on the base of them and not be totaly under water) since none of the wanderers would bother me there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Any way, the pet would follow me in. This way you can test the pet on all the green stuff on the shore.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Hmm, if ya want to split up the double spawns wouldnt you kill the 1st one as fast as possible by hard nuking then just healing the pet for the 2nd one to make the fight as long as possible, then keep doing this for a few spawns until they are split far apart.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Yep, that is the standard tactic of choice when breaking a double (or sometimes tripple) spawn.<br>
<br>
I have also had some success with double spawns by just fighting both at once and just healing the pet. That way the DS is ripping up both at once and by the time you finish nuking (to do half the damage) the first, the second is near half life making it easy to finish it too. That may not be possible with the Bloodgills.<br>
<br>
I think the worst part of a double spawn is the 2nd and third clearing where your're trying to get the timing just right. Usually it is somewhat mana inefficent to heal instead of nuke, so you end up using alot more mana <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Well, once you get the hang of it, come back and add some more to the thread, so when I can play again I'll know how to handle them! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
